{
    "key": "I",
    "title": "Interface definition (API)",
    "blocks": [
        {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Define a simple API contract: create job, fetch status, and deliver image URLs."
        },
        {
            "type": "divider"
        },
        {
            "type": "columns",
            "columns": [
                {
                    "blocks": [
                        {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "**How you should talk about the API:**\n\"I would expose a generate endpoint that returns a job id, then a status endpoint for polling or a stream endpoint for realtime updates.\""
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "blocks": [
                        {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "**What the interviewer listens for:**\n- Clear job lifecycle endpoints.\n- A simple polling or streaming strategy.\n- Output URLs for CDN delivery."
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "callout",
            "variant": "info",
            "title": "How you should act here",
            "text": "Keep the contract minimal: POST to create, GET to read status, and return a URL when done."
        },
        {
            "type": "divider"
        },
        {
            "type": "code",
            "language": "ts",
            "code": "POST /api/images/generate\n{ \"prompt\": \"a blue robot\" }\n\n200 OK\n{ \"jobId\": \"job_123\" }\n\nGET /api/images/jobs/job_123\n\n200 OK\n{ \"status\": \"running\", \"progress\": 0.4 }\n\n200 OK\n{ \"status\": \"done\", \"imageUrl\": \"https://cdn.example.com/img/123.png\" }\n\n// Optional streaming\nGET /api/images/jobs/job_123/stream (SSE)\nEVENT: progress\nDATA: { \"progress\": 0.4 }\nEVENT: done\nDATA: { \"imageUrl\": \"...\" }"
        },
        {
            "type": "table",
            "title": "Core interfaces you should define out loud",
            "columns": [
                "Interface / endpoint",
                "Shape (example)",
                "How you explain it"
            ],
            "rows": [
                [
                    "POST /generate",
                    "returns jobId",
                    "Creates a long-running job."
                ],
                [
                    "GET /jobs/:id",
                    "status + progress",
                    "UI polls until done."
                ],
                [
                    "GET /jobs/:id/stream",
                    "progress events",
                    "Optional realtime updates."
                ],
                [
                    "imageUrl",
                    "CDN URL",
                    "Result is served from object storage."
                ]
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "columns",
            "columns": [
                {
                    "blocks": [
                        {
                            "type": "checklist",
                            "title": "Things you should expose",
                            "items": [
                                "jobId and status",
                                "progress updates",
                                "imageUrl when done"
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "blocks": [
                        {
                            "type": "checklist",
                            "title": "Things you should NOT expose",
                            "items": [
                                "raw model internals",
                                "binary image blobs in API responses",
                                "long-lived polling without backoff"
                            ]
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        {
